Design Notes
============

The design is modeled on git, a database within the filesystem.

state/current is analogous to HEAD

tasks is analogous to the obj/ directory

The ID of a task is the date plus the slugified form of the name's first 16
characters. Example:

  design_session-2011_1_08

We use name then date so that autocompleting the ID makes more sense.


Filesystem layout
=================

.tt/
  ttconfig
    time_increment_minutes=15
  state/
    priority/
      top/
        design_session_2011_1_08
      high/
      low/
    status/
      pending/
        design_session_2011_1_08
      current/
          design_session_2011_1_08
      stopped/
      done/
      closed/
      deleted/
  tasks/
    2011/
      01/
        08/
          design_session
            Design Session
            pending <timestamp>
            started <timestamp>
            stopped <timestamp>
            done <timestamp>
            closed <timestamp>


Models
======

Task
  Attributes:
    id
    name
    status
    priority
    timelog
  
  Mutators:
    add(pending_time=now)
    start(start_time=now)
    stop(stop_time=now)
    done(done_time=now)
    close(close_time=now)

TaskManager
  Attributes:
    current
    priority = {"top": [], "high": [], "low": []}
    status = {"pending": [], "started": [], "stopped": [],
              "done": [], "closed": [], "deleted": []}
  Mutators: 
    task_id = add_task(task, status=pending)
    start_task(task_id)
    stop_current() 
    close_task(task_id)
    delete_task(task_id)

  Accessors:
    task_id = get_current()
    task = get_task_by_id(task_id)
    tasks = get_tasks_by_priority(priority)
    tasks = get_tasks_by_status(status)

